The paper deals with the problem of allocating items to agents with arbitrary valuation functions using sequential auctions with scrip money. This problem falls under the domain of game theory and mechanism design, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. The most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), which specifically deals with the intersection of computer science and game theory. The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which are covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with economic aspects such as social welfare and egalitarian welfare, which are covered by cs.EC (Economics and Computation). Finally, the paper involves analysis of equilibria, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning).
